<br>
A fresh gash marrs his playful, sunburned face; a bruise darkens the soft flesh beneath one eye. He cradles his sword like a baby. <br>
<br>
&quot;I just returned from war with the bandits in Paludal,&quot; he says as you sit down at the nearest table. &quot;I played tag with them in the darkness, was bodyguard to priest and wizard... but those caverns will never find peace. And I miss the sky.&quot; <br>
<br>
He sips his wine, gently, and with great relish. <br>
<br>
&quot;Before I came to the moon I always walked alone. The orcs in Faydark invented a curseword just for me. My friends gave me other names. The dwarves call me Stoneleaf. To the Kerrans I am Longwalker Badswimmer, and to the Centaurs I am Slowfoot Badbow. The barbarians... the Northmen call me That Boy, or sometimes Faenris's Son. And the elves don't really care for me, much. Can't say I blame them,&quot; he says, nearly a whisper. &quot;Mother and Father called me Lest.<br>
<br>
&quot;Lest-ye-forget Ravenfolly, ranger, swordsman, hunter, tracker, bodyguard, piss-poor archer,&quot; he says, extending his hand. &quot;Pleased to meet you.&quot; <br>
*******<br>
OOC: <br>
My ranger is lonely. <br>
<br>
I soloed exclusively for roughly twenty levels, tried to really learn my class... discovered grouping in Paludal and found I actually enjoy it, and did it long enough to trust myself around other players, which I didn't before. <br>
<br>
More than hunting companions I'm searching for folks to create story and mythos with. Never been guilded and never played a character this long before, on FV or any server, and I keep really inconsistent hours, so I don't know what the next step to take is -- s'why I'm posting here. <br>
<br>
Lest is a dreamer, but he's self-sacrificing and caring and earnest, has never judged a soul based on size or skin color (just don't kill a wolf in front of him -- that he finds horrifying). He has a bad relationship with his goddess. He is wickedly shy, especially around confident people. And pretty girls. And he tends to chew on mint leaves. All the time. If he sounds like the type of person you'd like to have a mug of ale with, he'd be glad to chat with you. <br>
<br>
Lest Ravenfolly<br>
